01:08:08.000 --> 01:08:10.000
That was called a tidy-up.

01:08:10.000 --> 01:08:12.000
It's sort of like a similar idea to

01:08:12.000 --> 01:08:14.000
like a pet for

01:08:14.000 --> 01:08:16.000
Quicken, where you say

01:08:16.000 --> 01:08:18.000
this is our problem.

01:08:18.000 --> 01:08:20.000
These are potential solutions.

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:22.000
We've gone with this one for this reason.

01:08:22.000 --> 01:08:24.000
This other idea that sounds really good

01:08:24.000 --> 01:08:26.000
did not work because of.

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:32.000
Sometimes these things

01:08:32.000 --> 01:08:34.000
are written up after the fact,

01:08:34.000 --> 01:08:36.000
but usually those are written up

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:38.000
before you make a decision to

01:08:38.000 --> 01:08:40.000
gather feedback.

01:08:40.000 --> 01:08:42.000
So if

01:08:42.000 --> 01:08:44.000
you're interested in

01:08:44.000 --> 01:08:46.000
like how

01:08:46.000 --> 01:08:48.000
we work, look for

01:08:48.000 --> 01:08:50.000
this kind of documentation.

01:08:50.000 --> 01:08:52.000
It is really like the guideline

01:08:52.000 --> 01:08:54.000
of how we do our work.

01:08:54.000 --> 01:08:56.000
And we make it public

01:08:56.000 --> 01:08:58.000
in case it is helpful for other people

01:08:58.000 --> 01:09:00.000
